                <head>211. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The United States and the Soviet Union signed two strategic arms limitation
                    accords on May 26, 1972: the Treaty on the Limitation of Anti-Ballistic Missile
                    Systems and the Interim Agreement on Certain Measures With Respect to the
                    Limitation of Strategic Offensive Arms. The former limited each signatory’s
                    deployment of anti-ballistic missile systems to two designated areas, including
                    the national command authority. The latter limited the overall level of
                    strategic offensive missile forces. For the full text of the agreements, see
                        <ref target="frus1969-76v32#d316">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume XXXII, <gloss
                            target="#t_SALT1">SALT</gloss> I, 1969–1972, Documents 316</ref>, <ref
                        target="frus1969-76v32#d317">317</ref>, and <ref
                        target="frus1969-76v32#d318">318</ref>.</p>
            </div>
